 Borussia Dortmund has set the price for Manchester United and Manchester City target Erling Braut Haaland for this summer transfer. The 20-year-old attacker is one of the most sought-after players in Europe after a sensational performance for Dortmund, where he scored 53 goals in 56 games. Chelsea star doubtful for return leg match against Real Madrid Mbappe prepares for a move away from Paris Saint-Germain Real Madrid is also one of the clubs interested in his services but it seems they have taken the back seat in the race to land the Norweigian star due to the impact of Covid-19. They must wait until next summer for Haaland’s €75m release clause to become activated. But should they want to bring forward their plans, Eurosport says clubs must pay €150m (£130m) for Dortmund’s prized asset. It is believed Haaland is leaning towards spending another season at Dortmund and could go for a fee less than what the club’s board is quoting for his value. Post Views: 
